org.javimmutable.collections

Interface JImmutableMultiset<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cursorable<T>, Insertable<T,JImmutableSet<T>>, InvariantCheckable, Iterable<T>, IterableStreamable<T>, JImmutableSet<T>, Mapped<T,T>, SplitableIterable<T>, Streamable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractJImmutableMultiset, JImmutableHashMultiset, JImmutableInsertOrderMultiset, JImmutableTreeMultiset

    @Immutable
public interface JImmutableMultiset<T>
extends JImmutableSet<T>
    Keeps a set of distinct values, as well as the count corresponding to each value. Can iterate through the multiset with the correct number of occurrences per value.

      • setCount

        @Nonnull
JImmutableMultiset<T> setCount(@Nonnull
                                        T value,
                                        int count)
        Manually sets the number of occurrences associated with the specified value. Count must be greater than or equal to zero. If count == 0, is synonymous to delete(value). If value is not currently in the multiset, is equivalent to insert(value, count).
        Parameters:
        value - value to add
        count - new number of occurrences for value
        Returns:
        new multiset reflecting the change
